        <div n="469-14W2" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">1729.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-1">A<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">N</hi> ass's hoof alone can hold</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-2"> That poisonous juice, which kills by cold.</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-3"> Methought, when I this poem read,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-4"> No vessel but an ass's head</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-5"> Such frigid fustian could contain;</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-6"> I mean, the head without the brain.</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-7"> The cold conceits, the chilling thoughts,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-8"> Went down like stupifying draughts;</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-9"> I found my head begin to swim,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-10"> A numbness crept through every limb.</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-11"> In haste, with imprecations dire,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-12"> I threw the volume in the fire;</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-13"> When, (who could think?) though cold as ice,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-14"> It burnt to ashes in a trice.How could I more enhance its fame?</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-469-14W2-line-15"> Though born in snow, it died in flame.469-14W2   </l></lg></div>
